---
// Article 1.3: Ambulance Services in Malaysia
import Layout from '../../../layouts/Layout.astro';
import Header from '../../../components/Header.astro';
import Footer from '../../../components/Footer.astro';
import AudienceTabs from '../../../components/AudienceTabs.astro';
import Breadcrumb from '../../../components/panduan-rakyat/Breadcrumb';

const articleData = {
  sectionNumber: '01',
  sectionTitle: 'Safety and Emergencies',
  sectionIcon: '🚨',
  articleTitle: 'Ambulance Services in Malaysia',
  articleDescription: 'Emergency medical services, how to call, and what to expect',
  colorRgb: '220, 38, 38',
  lastUpdated: 'March 2026',
};

const simpleContent = `
  <h2 id="what-is-ambulance">What is an ambulance for?</h2>
  <p>An ambulance is a special vehicle that brings medical help to you fast. The people inside are trained to give you medical care before you reach the hospital.</p>
  
  <h2 id="when-to-call">When should you call an ambulance?</h2>
  <ul>
    <li>Someone has fainted or is unconscious.</li>
    <li>Someone cannot breathe properly.</li>
    <li>Someone is having a heart attack or stroke.</li>
    <li>Someone is badly injured from an accident.</li>
    <li>Someone is in severe pain and cannot be moved safely.</li>
  </ul>

  <h2 id="what-number">What number do you call?</h2>
  <p>Call <strong>999</strong>. It is free. It works 24 hours a day, 7 days a week.</p>

  <h2 id="what-to-say">What do you say?</h2>
  <ol>
    <li><strong>Your name.</strong></li>
    <li><strong>Where you are</strong> (full address or nearest landmark).</li>
    <li><strong>What happened</strong> and how the person looks right now.</li>
    <li><strong>Whether the person is conscious and breathing.</strong></li>
  </ol>

  <h2 id="while-waiting">While waiting for the ambulance:</h2>
  <ul>
    <li>Keep the person still and calm.</li>
    <li>Do not give food or water.</li>
    <li>Do not move them unless there is immediate danger.</li>
    <li>Stay on the line with the operator if possible.</li>
  </ul>

  <h2 id="types-of-services">Types of ambulance services:</h2>
  <ul>
    <li><strong>Government ambulance</strong> - Free, for emergencies</li>
    <li><strong>St. John Ambulance (SJAM)</strong> - NGO, 24/7 service</li>
    <li><strong>Malaysian Red Crescent</strong> - NGO, community service</li>
    <li><strong>Private ambulance</strong> - For non-emergency transfers (paid)</li>
  </ul>
`;

const detailedContent = `
  <h2 id="overview">Overview</h2>
  <p>Ambulance services in Malaysia are provided by a mix of government, non-governmental, and private operators. The primary emergency number is 999, which dispatches the nearest available ambulance. Government ambulance services are free of charge and funded by public taxes.</p>

  <h2 id="when-to-use">When to Use Government vs Private Ambulance</h2>
  <table class="w-full border-collapse border border-border my-4">
    <thead>
      <tr class="bg-muted">
        <th class="border border-border p-3 text-left">Situation</th>
        <th class="border border-border p-3 text-left">Recommended Service</th>
      </tr>
    </thead>
    <tbody>
      <tr>
        <td class="border border-border p-3">Life-threatening emergency</td>
        <td class="border border-border p-3">Call 999. Government or SJAM/MRC dispatched.</td>
      </tr>
      <tr>
        <td class="border border-border p-3">Non-emergency hospital transfer</td>
        <td class="border border-border p-3">Private ambulance (SJAM, First Ambulance, MMR)</td>
      </tr>
      <tr>
        <td class="border border-border p-3">Outstation medical transport</td>
        <td class="border border-border p-3">Private ambulance with advance booking</td>
      </tr>
      <tr>
        <td class="border border-border p-3">Mass casualty or disaster</td>
        <td class="border border-border p-3">999 or 991 (Civil Defence coordination)</td>
      </tr>
    </tbody>
  </table>

  <h2 id="scenarios">Real Scenarios</h2>
  
  <h3 id="scenario-1">Scenario 1: Encik Subramaniam collapses at home</h3>
  <p>Encik Subramaniam, 67, collapsed in his living room. His wife panicked and considered driving him to the hospital herself. His son stopped her and called 999 instead. The operator guided them through basic first aid while the ambulance was dispatched. The ambulance arrived in 12 minutes and the paramedics stabilised him en route to the hospital.</p>

  <h3 id="scenario-2">Scenario 2: Road accident on the North-South Expressway</h3>
  <p>A multi-vehicle accident occurred near Rawang. A witness called 999 and specified multiple injured persons. The operator coordinated PDRM, BOMBA, and ambulance dispatch simultaneously. Bystanders were advised not to move the injured until paramedics arrived.</p>

  <h3 id="scenario-3">Scenario 3: Non-emergency transfer for Puan Halimah</h3>
  <p>Puan Halimah needed to be transferred from a government hospital in Ipoh to a specialist centre in KL for a planned procedure. Her family arranged a private ambulance through First Ambulance with 48 hours advance notice. The cost was approximately RM420 for the night transfer.</p>

  <h2 id="what-to-do">What To Do: Step by Step</h2>
  <ol>
    <li><strong>Call 999</strong> - Stay calm, speak clearly</li>
    <li><strong>Describe the condition</strong> - Be specific about symptoms</li>
    <li><strong>Follow operator instructions</strong> - They may guide you through first aid</li>
    <li><strong>Meet ambulance at entrance</strong> - Wave them down if possible</li>
    <li><strong>Bring essentials</strong> - IC, medical records, medications if time permits</li>
  </ol>

  <h2 id="costs">Costs</h2>
  <ul>
    <li><strong>Government ambulance (999):</strong> FREE</li>
    <li><strong>SJAM / Red Crescent:</strong> FREE for emergencies, nominal fee for event standby</li>
    <li><strong>Private ambulance:</strong> RM200-800 depending on distance and services</li>
  </ul>

  <h2 id="important-numbers">Important Numbers</h2>
  <ul>
    <li><strong>999</strong> - General emergency (ambulance, police, fire)</li>
    <li><strong>991</strong> - Civil Defence (disaster emergencies)</li>
    <li><strong>St. John Ambulance:</strong> 03-2274 4911</li>
    <li><strong>Malaysian Red Crescent:</strong> 03-2691 3922</li>
  </ul>
`;

const faqs = [
  {
    question: "Is calling 999 for ambulance free?",
    answer: "Yes, calling 999 for ambulance services is completely free. Government ambulance services are funded by public taxes."
  },
  {
    question: "How long does an ambulance take to arrive?",
    answer: "Target response time is 15 minutes in urban areas. Rural areas may take longer. During peak traffic or major incidents, delays can occur."
  },
  {
    question: "Can I request a specific hospital?",
    answer: "Yes, you can request a hospital, but paramedics may take you to the nearest appropriate facility based on your condition and traffic conditions."
  },
  {
    question: "What if I need an ambulance for non-emergency transfer?",
    answer: "For non-emergency transfers (e.g., between hospitals), contact private ambulance services like St. John Ambulance, First Ambulance, or MMR Ambulance. Expect to pay RM200-800 depending on distance."
  },
  {
    question: "Can family members ride in the ambulance?",
    answer: "Usually one family member can ride in the front passenger seat if space allows. This is at the discretion of the paramedics based on the patient's condition."
  }
];

const headings = [
  { id: 'overview', title: 'Overview', level: 2 },
  { id: 'when-to-use', title: 'When to Use Government vs Private', level: 2 },
  { id: 'scenarios', title: 'Real Scenarios', level: 2 },
  { id: 'what-to-do', title: 'What To Do: Step by Step', level: 2 },
  { id: 'costs', title: 'Costs', level: 2 },
  { id: 'important-numbers', title: 'Important Numbers', level: 2 },
];
---

<Layout title={`${articleData.articleTitle} | People's Guide | EduLaluan`}>
  <Header />

  <main class="min-h-screen bg-background">
    <!-- Article Header -->
    <section 
      class="relative overflow-hidden py-section-lg border-b"
      style={{
        '--section-color': `rgb(${articleData.colorRgb})`,
        'border-bottom-color': `rgb(${articleData.colorRgb})`
      }}
    >
      <div class="container mx-auto px-4 sm:px-6 lg:px-8">
        <div class="max-w-4xl">
          <!-- Breadcrumb -->
          <Breadcrumb items={[
            { label: 'Home', href: '/' },
            { label: "People's Guide", href: '/panduan-rakyat' },
            { label: `Section ${articleData.sectionNumber}`, href: `/panduan-rakyat/section-${articleData.sectionNumber}` },
            { label: articleData.articleTitle }
          ]} />

          <!-- Back Button -->
          <a
            href={`/panduan-rakyat/section-${articleData.sectionNumber}`}
            class="inline-flex items-center gap-2 text-sm text-muted-foreground hover:text-primary transition-colors mb-6"
          >
            <svg class="w-4 h-4" fill="none" viewBox="0 0 24 24" stroke="currentColor">
              <path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-width="2" d="M15 19l-7-7 7-7" />
            </svg>
            Back to Section {parseInt(articleData.sectionNumber).toString()}
          </a>

          <!-- Article Title -->
          <div class="flex items-start gap-4 mt-6">
            <div 
              class="flex h-16 w-16 shrink-0 items-center justify-center rounded-xl text-3xl"
              style={{ 
                'backgroundColor': `rgb(${articleData.colorRgb})`,
                'color': 'white'
              }}
            >
              {articleData.sectionIcon}
            </div>
            <div class="flex-1">
              <p class="text-sm font-medium text-primary mb-1 tracking-wide uppercase">
                Section {parseInt(articleData.sectionNumber).toString()}: {articleData.sectionTitle}
              </p>
              <h1 class="font-display text-3xl sm:text-4xl font-bold text-foreground">
                {articleData.articleTitle}
              </h1>
              <p class="text-lg text-muted-foreground mt-3">
                {articleData.articleDescription}
              </p>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <!-- Article Content -->
    <section class="py-section-md bg-surface">
      <div class="container mx-auto px-4 sm:px-6 lg:px-8">
        <div class="flex gap-8 max-w-6xl mx-auto">
          <!-- Main Content -->
          <div class="flex-1 min-w-0">
            <!-- Audience Tabs (Simple/Detailed) -->
            <AudienceTabs>
              <Fragment slot="simple" set:html={simpleContent} />
              <Fragment slot="detailed" set:html={detailedContent} />
            </AudienceTabs>

            <!-- FAQ Section -->
            <div class="mt-12">
              <h2 class="font-display text-2xl font-bold text-foreground mb-6">
                Frequently Asked Questions
              </h2>
              <div class="space-y-3">
                {faqs.map((faq) => (
                  <details
                    class="group rounded-xl border bg-surface-elevated transition-all"
                  >
                    <summary class="flex cursor-pointer items-center justify-between p-5 font-semibold text-foreground list-none">
                      {faq.question}
                      <svg
                        class="h-5 w-5 text-muted-foreground transition-transform group-open:rotate-180"
                        fill="none"
                        viewBox="0 0 24 24"
                        stroke="currentColor"
                      >
                        <path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-width="2" d="M19 9l-7 7-7-7" />
                      </svg>
                    </summary>
                    <div class="px-5 pb-5 text-muted-foreground">
                      {faq.answer}
                    </div>
                  </details>
                ))}
              </div>
            </div>

            <!-- Last Updated -->
            <div class="mt-12 pt-6 border-t border-border">
              <p class="text-sm text-muted-foreground">
                <strong>Last updated:</strong> {articleData.lastUpdated}
              </p>
            </div>
          </div>

          <!-- Table of Contents (Sidebar) -->
          <aside class="sticky top-24 hidden lg:block w-64 shrink-0">
            <nav class="space-y-1" aria-label="Table of contents">
              <h3 class="text-xs font-semibold text-muted-foreground uppercase tracking-wide mb-3">
                On This Page
              </h3>
              {headings.map((heading) => (
                <a
                  href={`#${heading.id}`}
                  class="block py-1.5 text-sm text-muted-foreground hover:text-foreground transition-colors"
                  style={{ paddingLeft: `${(heading.level - 2) * 12 + 12}px` }}
                >
                  {heading.title}
                </a>
              ))}
            </nav>
          </aside>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <!-- Navigation Footer -->
    <section class="py-section-md bg-background">
      <div class="container mx-auto px-4 sm:px-6 lg:px-8">
        <div class="mx-auto max-w-4xl">
          <div class="rounded-2xl border bg-surface-elevated p-6">
            <div class="flex items-center gap-3 text-muted-foreground">
              <svg class="w-5 h-5" fill="none" viewBox="0 0 24 24" stroke="currentColor">
                <path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-width="2" d="M13 16h-1v-4h-1m1-4h.01M21 12a9 9 0 11-18 0 9 9 0 0118 0z" />
              </svg>
              <p class="text-sm">
                <strong>Disclaimer:</strong> This guide provides general information only. Always verify with official sources for the most current information.
              </p>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>
  </main>

  <Footer />
</Layout>

<style>
  /* Section padding utilities */
  :root {
    --section-padding-lg: clamp(3rem, 5vw + 1rem, 5rem);
    --section-padding-md: clamp(2rem, 3vw + 1rem, 3rem);
  }

  .py-section-lg {
    padding-top: var(--section-padding-lg);
    padding-bottom: var(--section-padding-lg);
  }

  .py-section-md {
    padding-top: var(--section-padding-md);
    padding-bottom: var(--section-padding-md);
  }

  /* Article Typography */
  .prose-panduan {
    font-size: var(--text-base);
    line-height: var(--leading-relaxed);
    color: var(--foreground);
  }

  .prose-panduan h2 {
    font-family: var(--font-display);
    font-size: var(--text-2xl);
    font-weight: 700;
    margin-top: 2.5rem;
    margin-bottom: 1rem;
    color: var(--foreground);
  }

  .prose-panduan h3 {
    font-family: var(--font-display);
    font-size: var(--text-xl);
    font-weight: 600;
    margin-top: 2rem;
    margin-bottom: 0.75rem;
    color: var(--foreground);
  }

  .prose-panduan p {
    margin-bottom: 1.25rem;
  }

  .prose-panduan ul,
  .prose-panduan ol {
    margin-bottom: 1.25rem;
    padding-left: 1.5rem;
  }

  .prose-panduan li {
    margin-bottom: 0.5rem;
  }

  .prose-panduan a {
    color: var(--primary);
    text-decoration: underline;
    text-underline-offset: 2px;
  }

  .prose-panduan a:hover {
    color: var(--primary-dark);
  }

  .prose-panduan strong {
    font-weight: 600;
    color: var(--foreground);
  }

  .prose-panduan table {
    width: 100%;
    border-collapse: collapse;
    margin: 1.5rem 0;
  }

  .prose-panduan th {
    background-color: var(--muted);
    font-weight: 600;
    padding: 0.75rem;
    border: 1px solid var(--border);
  }

  .prose-panduan td {
    padding: 0.75rem;
    border: 1px solid var(--border);
  }
</style>
